overview: The user initiated a request to elevate the aesthetic appeal of their
  sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was visually uninspired. The
  assistant conducted a detailed analysis of the existing design, identifying
  areas such as the generic color palette, basic UI components, and inconsistent
  section styling. A new, calming sleep-themed color palette was introduced,
  along with custom CSS utilities for gradients and shadows. The main form
  layout was redesigned with subtle background elements and an enhanced progress
  indicator. All form fields and UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons,
  and sliders received significant styling updates to provide better visual
  feedback and a more cohesive look. Furthermore, all questionnaire sections
  were standardized with the new theme, replacing old gray boxes with refined
  card-like groupings. During a post-implementation review, a console error
  related to null input values was identified and promptly fixed in the
  component. Additional aesthetic refinements were made to alert colors and
  section border opacities. The comprehensive effort transformed the app from a
  generic interface into a professional, visually appealing, and trustworthy
  sleep health assessment tool.
